latestPosts.caption:
Not sure what to do about stretch marks?

You’re not alone and you don’t have to hide them or live with discomfort in silence.

Let’s break it down simply, from what causes them to how you can treat them effectively and rebuild skin from within. 💫

- What causes stretch marks: Rapid changes like pregnancy or weight fluctuations stretch the skin too quickly, leading to tiny tears in the deeper dermal layer.

- Why creams don’t work: Most only hydrate the surface. Real repair happens deeper, where the collagen has been disrupted.

- What actually works: At Leor, we use Morpheus treatment that combines microneedling and radiofrequency to stimulate collagen from within and visibly reduce stretch marks.

Your stretch marks are not flaws, they are proof of your strength. Whether you choose to treat them or wear them with pride, we’re here to support your journey. ✨💫

#LeorClinics #StretchMarkTreatment #CollagenRepair #SkinConfidence #HealWithLeor #WomensWellness #Morpheus8 #StretchMarksAreNormal

Think you might have PCOS but not sure what to do next?

You’re not alone and you don’t have to figure it out by yourself.

Let’s break it down simply, from what tests to get, to the signs your body’s been showing you and how small lifestyle shifts can help you take back control. 💜

🔍 How to test for PCOS: The 3 essential steps you need to follow, including a hormone blood test, pelvic ultrasound and tracking your symptoms.

⚠️ Symptoms to watch: Irregular periods, acne, facial hair, weight gain and hair fall, even if your periods seem ‘normal’, PCOS can still be affecting you silently.

🧘‍♀️ Daily habits to manage it: Gentle movement, balanced meals with more protein and fiber, cutting down sugar and most importantly regulating your sleep cycle.

At Leor Clinics, we believe awareness is the first step and real care begins with consistent and doable changes tailored to you.

PCOS is manageable and you’ve got this. 💪

#LeorClinics #PCOSAwareness #HormoneBalance #WomensHealthMatters #HealWithLeor #LifestyleMedicine #PCOSSupport

2) Retinol - PM (only at night)
	•	Boosts collagen production 
	•	Targets fine lines, wrinkles 

3) Vitamin C + Sunscreen - AM (only during the day)
	•	Vitamin C brightens the  skin 
	•	Sunscreen protect against harmful UV rays
